This paper deals with the geometric properties of polyhedra and their unfoldings, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves partitioning the polyhedron into convex polygons, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of geodesic convex polygons is related to the study of graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the spanning tree of the edge skeleton, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the problem of finding non-overlapping unfoldings is related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
